House Resolution 56
By: Representatives Petrea of the 166th and Stephens of the 164th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing January 28, 2025, as Bryan Day at the state capitol; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, presented by the Bryan County Chamber of Commerce and the Development
3 Authority of Bryan County, Bryan Day represents an opportunity to celebrate the rich history
4 and remarkable contributions of Bryan County, Georgia; and
5 WHEREAS, created on December 19, 1793, and named after American Revolutionary War
6 partisan Jonathan Bryan, Bryan County is located less than 30 minutes from Savannah-Hilton
7 Head International Airport and the Port of Savannah; and
8 WHEREAS, Bryan County is unique in that one-third of the community is occupied by Fort
9 Stewart, the largest army installation east of the Mississippi River and home of the 3rd
10 Infantry Division; and
11 WHEREAS, the City of Pembroke serves as the county seat and offers residents a rural
12 setting in the northern portion of the county, while the City of Richmond Hill covers the
13 southern end of the county and rests on the Georgia coast; and
